    "body" : "Remember two more things: 1) The mere mention of a decompiler will cause the &quot;holier than thou&#39;s&quot; to come out and make value judgements about your motives despite having no idea what your planned use is, so be careful who you talk to.  2) The fancy JavaDecompiler will give you an excellent rendition of the code, well laid out and easy to read - missing only comments.  It is astoundingly good, recovering a JAR file which had long lost source complete with variable names.  Of course we don&#39;t obfuscate our in-house JAR files."
